Business Brief -- Midlantic Corp.:
   Bank Holding Concern Says
   Loss Widened in 4th Period
Net interest income fell 23% to $143.6 million from a year
earlier, while non-interest expense grew 23% to $190 million.
Non-interest income rose 15% to $69.4 million.
   The bank took a loan-loss provision of $109 million, up
from $41 million in the third quarter, but down from $115
million in the 1990 fourth quarter. The total loanloss
provision rose to 67% of nonperforming loans from 64%.